Just got back from vacation which included a week as a delegate to the VVA National Convention.  Am checking the threads from the top down.  If the above is a sample; I haven't missed much.....Cook making like the the ultimate macho super patriotic Marine (and there are other varieties) with encouragement from Edward, and Doc having furious conniptions over Cook's posts.  I wish Cook would use some of the sensitivity he puts into his poetry toward those who didn't get gung ho to fight in Vietnam.  They're not necessarily cowardly or morally deficient.  It's one thing to believe someone is wrong; quite another to assume someone's motives are rotten.  The &quot;Commie Gook&quot; BS is getting old.  As for Doc: Yo, this ain't nothin'. You should see what it's like when you can't get a Marine the aircraft parts he needed yesterday, more than the entire Navy fleet.  Besides, I half suspect he's baiting you by taking his views to the max. 
